"If Ben, Jeff, and Louise all sign up for accounts on GitHub, and you want to give them push access to your repository, you can add them to your project.\n"
"Doing so will give them \"`push`\" access, which means they have both read and write access to the project and Git repository.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: book/06-github/sections/3-maintaining.asc:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "Click the \"`Settings`\" link at the bottom of the right-hand sidebar.\n"
